<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gamecocks' Skip Holtz Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) -- South Carolina offensive coordinator Skip  
Holtz, son of coach Lou Holtz, was hospitalized with stomach pains 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was in pain Thursday and it kept getting worse,'' Lou Holtz  
said. ``We don't know what it is.'' 
</P>
<P>
	If Skip's condition keeps him out, his father would take a more  
active role in an offense that looked feeble and mistake prone in a 
10-0 loss to North Carolina State Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Gamecocks committed eight fumbles, losing four, and  
quarterback Phil Petty threw an interception and struggled to keep 
the ball from squirting out of his hands in the soggy conditions. 
</P>
<P>
	Without his offensive coaching leader, Lou Holtz said he would  
get more involved in South Carolina's attack. 
</P>
<P>
	``I can't tell you how many games I've coached how few times  
I've been shut out,'' the coach said. ``I haven't been to bed yet, 
I can't sleep after losses. I am going to be more intense than I've 
ever been.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
