<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Smart Guy Wins Pennsylvania Derby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BENSALEM, Pa. (AP) -- After losing the lead with a furlong to go,  
Smart Guy came on a second time and beat Ghost Ring by a head to 
win the $300,000 Pennsylvania Derby at Philadelphia Park on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Bobby Colton, the bay colt, which was purchased from a  
sale in Maryland two years ago for $10,000, went right to the front 
of the 10-horse field and set the pace for the first mile of the 
1 1/8-mile race for 3-year-olds. 
</P>
<P>
	Ghost Ring, ridden by Aaron Gryder, took the lead after a mile  
and ran with Smart Guy second for about 20 yards, then Smart Guy 
came on again. 
</P>
<P>
	With Ghost Ring on the outside and Smart Guy on the rail, the  
colts battled head to head to the wire with Smart Guy getting there 
first in 1:49 2-5. 
</P>
<P>
	Pineaff, the winner of the Tampa Bay Derby and a ninth-place  
finisher in the Belmont Stakes, closed ground on the leaders in the 
stretch but was another five lengths back in third. 
</P>
<P>
	Smart Guy earned $180,000 to raise his lifetime total to  
$373,290 for the Goodfellas Stable of Wilmington, Del. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
