<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Hernandez Exits With Rib Tightness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- San Francisco's Livan Hernandez left Monday's  
game against the New York Mets with tightness in his rib cage. 
</P>
<P>
	The right-hander threw one warmup pitch in the bottom of the  
third inning of the scoreless game before grabbing his left side. 
Giants manager Dusty Baker and a trainer went to the mound to check 
Hernandez before taking him out of the game and replacing him with 
Mark Gardner. X-rays were negative, and he will be re-evaluated 
when the team returns to San Francisco on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Hernandez hit a long drive to right field in the top of the  
third and may have injured himself swinging. 
</P>
<P>
	Hernandez (7-11) went two innings, allowed one hit and struck  
out one. Acquired from Florida on July 24 for minor league pitchers 
Jason Grilli and Nate Bump, he is 0-5 in five starts against the 
Mets this season. He is 2-6 in 11 career starts against them. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
