<HEADLINE> Pirates Recall Prospect Hermansen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Chad Hermansen, Pittsburgh's top prospect, and  
third baseman Aramis Ramirez are among five minor league players 
who will be added to the Pirates' active roster Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Pirates have recalled Hermansen, Ramirez and right-hander  
Jason Boyd from Triple-A Nashville. Boyd was acquired from Arizona 
last month as the player to be named later in the Tony Womack 
trade. 
</P>
<P>
	They also purchased the contracts of right-hander Mike Garcia  
from the Mexico City Red Devils of the Mexican League and catcher 
Tim Laker of Nashville. 
</P>
<P>
	Pirates manager Gene Lamont said that Hermansen, an outfielder  
who had 32 homers and 97 RBIs at Nashville, would make his first 
major league start Tuesday night against San Diego left-hander 
Sterling Hitchcock. 
</P>
<P>
	Ramirez, who was the Pirates' starting third baseman last season  
for a brief time, was hitting .327 with 21 homers and 74 RBIs at 
Nashville. 
  	   	
</P>
