<HEADLINE> Imported Vehicle Sales Up in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Sales of imported vehicles rose 3 percent in August  
from the same month last year, an industry association announced 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Importers sold a total of 17,086 cars, trucks and buses last  
month, compared with 16,588 sold in August last year, the Japan 
Automobile Importers Association said. 
</P>
<P>
	The August increase in imports followed a 5.9-percent  
year-on-year drop in July, a 15.8-percent rise in June and a 
0.2-percent fall in May. 
</P>
<P>
	For August, the association said imported passenger cars rose  
3.2 percent to 16,422 while truck imports fell 2.4 percent to 662. 
Sales of buses in August totaled 2, compared with 3 buses sold a 
year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	The figures come as Japan is struggling to emerge from its worst  
economic downturn in 50 years. 
</P>
<P>
	German automakers sold a total of 9,107 vehicles in August, down  
0.4 percent from a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales of U.S.-made vehicles, which totaled 3,727, were up 15.4  
percent. They were followed by British automobiles, which totaled 
sales of 1,447, up 7 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Swedish automakers sold 789 vehicles, down 6 percent, and French  
carmakers sold 707, down 3.4 percent. Sales of Italian cars in 
Japan totaled 501 in August, down 4.4 percent. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
