<HEADLINE>  Sammy Sosa Hits 58th Home Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Sammy Sosa hit his major league leading 58th  
homer Monday, giving him a four-homer lead over Mark McGwire. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa drove a 2-1 third-inning pitch from Cincinnati's Juan  
Guzman over the left-field wall and onto Waveland Avenue. The drive 
came against a 15 mph wind blowing in at Wrigley Field. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa is six games ahead of his pace during his 66-homer season  
last year. His 58th last season came in Chicago's 142nd game. The 
Cubs played their 136th game Monday and have 26 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Sosa's 30th homer this season at home.  
</P>
</TEXT>
