<HEADLINE> Rangers Sign Top Two Picks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Rangers agreed to terms with both  
of their first-round draft picks Monday, right wing Pavel Brendl 
and center Jamie Lundmark. 
</P>
<P>
	Brendl, 18, was chosen fourth overall in June's NHL entry draft,  
while Lundmark, also 18, was selected ninth. The Rangers acquired 
the fourth pick from the Tampa Bay Lightning for goalie Dan 
Cloutier, forward Niklas Sundstrom and first and third-round picks 
in 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	New York also moved up from 11th to ninth to take Lundmark,  
giving up center Marc Savard and acquiring the rights to Calgary 
Flames left wing Jan Hlavac and a third-round pick in the process. 
</P>
<P>
	Brendl led the Calgary Hitmen of the Western Hockey League with  
a league-leading 73 goals along with 61 assists in 68 games last 
season, also leading the league with a plus-68 rating. The 6-foot, 
200-pound Czech native made the WHL All-Star team while capturing 
rookie of the year honors. 
</P>
<P>
	Lundmark, who also played in the WHL last season, was second on  
the Moose Jaw Warriors with 91 points (40 goals, 51 assists) in 70 
games. 
  	   	
</P>
