<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wife of Umpire Who Lost Job Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GRAHAM, N.C. (AP) -- Kim Coble, the wife of an American League  
umpire who lost his job last week, died Sunday of cancer. She was 
44. 
</P>
<P>
	She is survived by her husband, Drew Coble, 51, and two  
children, Jason Bryant and Kiersten. 
</P>
<P>
	Coble was one of 22 umpires whose resignations, which were  
effective last Thursday, were accepted by major league baseball. He 
disputed that he tendered his resignation as part of a failed 
strategy by the umpires' union to force baseball to negotiate. 
</P>
<P>
	Coble was listed as one of the umpires who turned in their  
resignations on July 14. But he contended he never signed a letter 
of resignation. The umpires' union will try to regain the jobs in 
arbitration. 
</P>
<P>
	Coble had worked sparingly this season because of his wife's  
illness. 
</P>
<P>
	A funeral will be held Tuesday at Mount Hermon United Methodist  
Church. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
