<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Crafty Friends Wins Forgeo Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- After battling evenly from the  
start, Crafty Friend beat Affirmed Success by a neck Monday to win 
the $250,000 Forego Handicap at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
	Sir Bear was another length back in third in the field of nine.  
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Gary Stevens and carrying co-high weight of 119  
pounds, the 6-year-old Crafty Friend covered seven furlongs in 
1:21:1, the second fastest time in the 20 runnings of the race. 
Quick Call won the 1988 race in 1:21. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the third in six starts this year for Crafty Friend,  
who earned $150,000 for Ahmed bin Salman. 
</P>
<P>
	Crafty Friend returned $11.20, $4.50 and $3.40. Affirmed Success  
paid $4.10 and $2.90, while Sir Bear was $3.70 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
