<DOCNO> APW19990906.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 20:06:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Streep Learns Violin for Craven Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VENICE, Italy (AP) -- Meryl Streep in a movie by the man who gave  
us ``Scream''? 
</P>
<P>
	Look for her in the lead role of Wes Craven's ``Music of the  
Heart,'' a sentimental story about a violinist who teaches music in 
a Harlem school. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think that Craven's young fans who love blood and horror  
will be shocked by this film,'' Streep told RAI state TV. 
</P>
<P>
	She was in town Monday for a screening of the movie at the  
Venice Film Festival, which runs through Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Known for being a perfectionist, Streep said she studied violin  
for two months before shooting began. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am much less attentive to detail in my work than I was in  
the past. I don't consider this positive but this way I am able to 
spend more time with my children,'' Streep told the Italian news 
agency ANSA. 
</P>
<P>
	Madonna was originally going to star. The movie was several  
months into pre-production last year when she quit, citing creative 
differences with Craven. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
