	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Darryl Strawberry hit his first home run  
in more than a year, and Derek Jeter went 4-for-5 with a homer as 
the New York Yankees beat the Anaheim Angels 8-3 yesterday. 
Strawberry, who rejoined the team four games ago after a 113-day 
drug suspension, also had an RBI double. Rookie Ed Yarnall won his 
first major league start for the Yanks. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by VINCENT CINISOMO  




  	   	
