<HEADLINE> Marcel Wust Wins Tour of Spain Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ALBACETE, Spain (AP) -- Germany's Marcel Wust sprinted to victory  
in the second stage of the Tour of Spain Monday, while Frenchman 
Jacky Durand retained the overall lead. 
</P>
<P>
	Wust completed the 128-mile stage through eastern Spain in 4  
hours, 45 minutes, 5 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	Italy's Stefano Zanini was second and compatriot Giovanni  
Lombardi third after a mass sprint to the finish. 
</P>
<P>
	Spanish favorite Abraham Olano remained third overall, 3 seconds  
behind Durand. 
</P>
<P>
	During most of the second stage, the pack raced under heavy hail  
and rain. 
</P>
<P>
	The Tour will cover its longest stretch, 142 miles, on Tuesday  
from La Roda to Fuenlabrada in the outskirts of Madrid. 
  	   	
