<HEADLINE> Flyers Re-sign Zelepukin, Berube </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Forwards Valeri Zelepukin and Craig Berube  
have signed one-year contracts with the Philadelphia Flyers, team 
president and general manager Bob Clarke said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Zelepukin, 30, had 16 goals and 9 assists for 25 points in 74  
games for the Flyers last season. The eight-year NHL veteran has 
appeared in 482 career games with the Flyers, Edmonton and New 
Jersey, recording 103 goals and 152 assists for 255 points. 
</P>
<P>
	Berube, 33, had 28 penalty minutes in 11 games for the Flyers  
after being acquired from Washington in exchange for future 
considerations on March 23, 1999. 
</P>
<P>
	The 13-year NHL veteran has appeared in 796 games with the  
Flyers, Washington, Calgary and Toronto, recording 52 goals and 82 
assists for 134 points and 2,651 penalty minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the contracts were not disclosed.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
