<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fatal Float Crash Mars NYC Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Two 11-year-old children dancing in a parade  
celebrating Caribbean culture were killed Monday when they were hit 
by a float behind them. 
</P>
<P>
	Hours later, after the parade was over, an 18-year-old man was  
killed by a float along the parade route. Police did not release 
details. 
</P>
<P>
	In the first incident, Joseph Donn and Zacehel David were  
dancing behind a float attached to a truck that stopped suddenly. 
The driver of the next float couldn't stop in time and hit the 
children, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver that stopped suddenly was arrested on a charge of  
driving with a suspended license, police said. Four people, 
including two 10-year-old children, were taken to the hospital with 
minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	Hundreds of thousands of people from more than 12 island nations  
lined streets in Brooklyn for the annual West Indian American 
Carnival Parade, one of the city's largest ethnic festivals. 
</P>
<P>
	Caribbean immigrants wore the flags of their homelands as capes,  
donned brightly colored costumes with feathery headwear and sipped 
Jamaican beer and sugar cane drinks. Crowds waved flags and danced 
to pounding steel drums and calypso. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
