<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 15:50:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Best of the Rest Wins at Calder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Heavily favored Best of the Rest ran away with the  
$100,000 Spend A Buck Handicap on a sloppy track at Calder on 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Best of the Rest, jockey Eibar Coa's fourth winner of the day,  
took the lead on the final turn and finished 9 1/2 lengths in front of 
Dancing Guy. High Security was third in the field of 10 older 
horses. 
</P>
<P>
	Best of the Rest is 3-for-3 on off tracks. The only time he has  
finished out of the money in 12 lifetime starts was in his one race 
on the turf. He has won seven times, earning $242,139. He won three 
stakes at Calder last year but did not make his first start of 1999 
until Aug. 9. 
</P>
<P>
	The 4-year-old Florida-bred ran 1 1-16 miles in 1:44 3/5 and  
paid $4, $3.40 and $2.80. 
</P>
<P>
	Dancing Guy paid $11.80 and $6.20, while High Security was $3.40  
to show. 
</P>
<P>
	High Security broke on top with Best of the Rest right there on  
the inside. Turning down the backstretch High Security led by a 
length over Shamrock City with Best of the Rest third on the rail, 
followed by Fig Fest. At the half-mile pole High Security was in 
front by 1 1/2 lengths as the favorite came off the rail for running 
room. 
</P>
<P>
	Moving between High Security and Fig Fest, Best of the Rest took  
the lead at the quarter-pole and was all by himself from the 
eighth-pole to the wire. Dancing Guy rallied into second in 
mid-stretch and beat High Security by 1 1/2 lengths. Fig Fest was a 
half-farther back. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
