<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Stock Market at Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATHENS, Greece (AP) -- Greece's booming stock market soared into  
record territory Monday after Premier Costas Simitis predicted the 
exchange's growth would continue. 
</P>
<P>
	The Athens Stock Exchange's general index jumped to 5621.67  
points, up 213.82 points or 4 percent, with many shares hitting the 
8 percent daily increase limit. 
</P>
<P>
	Simitis, outlining economic policy over the weekend, announced  
sweeping tax cuts and said additional money would be raised by 
doubling taxes on stocks sales. His remarks eased concern that 
share values had peaked. 
</P>
<P>
	Hundreds of thousands of small investors have flocked to the  
high-flying Athens Stock Exchange over the past two years. The 
surge was aided by falling interest rates ahead of Greece's 
anticipated entry into the European Union's single currency group. 
</P>
<P>
	Greece is the only EU country that sought entry into the euro  
zone but failed to qualify for the initial group. Inflation and 
other factors have been brought in line and Greece is expected to 
join the group in 2001. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
