<HEADLINE> Alabama Suspends Two Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TUSCALOOSA, Ala. (AP) -- Alabama linebackers Darius Gilbert and  
Chris Horne have been suspended for Saturday's game against Houston 
for violating team rules. 
</P>
<P>
	It marks the second straight week Crimson Tide linebackers will  
be sitting out with suspensions. Horne, Miguel Merritt and Canary 
Knight were suspended for last Saturday's 28-17 win at Vanderbilt. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Mike DuBose said Monday the latest suspensions were  
unrelated to academic reasons that kept the three out last week. 
</P>
<P>
	Horne is normally Merritt's backup at outside linebacker.  
Gilbert started in Merritt's absence last week and had seven 
tackles. 
</P>
<P>
	Merritt, who along with Knight was welcomed back to the team  
Monday, is expected to start against Houston, alongside redshirt 
freshman Marvin Constant and freshman Saleem Rasheed. 
</P>
<P>
	Merritt and Knight said Monday their suspensions were for  
failing to complete enough credit hours last fall and both were 
given the option of missing last year's Music City Bowl or this 
year's season opener. 
  	   	
</P>
