<HEADLINE> Long Shot Wins Cradle Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Deputy Warlock, a 38-to-1 long shot, charged  
from 10th at the half-mile marker and caught favored Mighty in the 
final few yards Monday to win the $200,000 Cradle Stakes at River 
Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	With Fabio Arguello aboard, Deputy Warlock won the race for  
2-year-olds by a half-length and returned $79, $21 and $8. The 
horse covered the mile and 1-16 in 1:47 4-5. 
</P>
<P>
	Mighty, ridden by Pat Day, caught Personal First down the  
backstretch but couldn't hold on at the end, returning $2.80 and 
$2.40. 
</P>
<P>
	Personal First finished two lengths behind Mighty and paid  
$2.80. 
  	   	
</P>
