<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Val Royal Wins Del Mar Derby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Val Royal, the 3-2 favorite, overtook  
Fighting Falcon in the final strides to win Monday's $300,000 Del 
Mar Derby by a half-length. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Corey Nakatani, Val Royal covered 1 1/8 miles on turf in  
1:48 2-5 and paid $5, $3.20 and $2.80. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the fifth in seven lifetime starts for Val Royal and  
was worth $180,000, raising the career earnings of the 3-year-old 
French-bred son of Royal Academy to $315,644. 
</P>
<P>
	Val Royal, owned by television producer David Milch and trained  
by Julio Canani, ran his six previous races in France, the most 
recent on Aug. 14. 
</P>
<P>
	Fighting Falcon, ridden by Chris McCarron, crossed the finish  
line 1 1/4 lengths in front of In Frank's Honor and returned $4.60 and 
$3.60. 
</P>
<P>
	In Frank's Honor, ridden by Chris Antley, was 1 1/2 lengths ahead  
of Eagleton at the wire and paid $3.80 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Following Eagleton across the finish line in the 55th running of  
the race for 3-year-olds were Zanetti, Major Hero, Domination, 
Roundabout, Walk That Walk and Make Your Mark. Each of the 10 
entries carried 121 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Ladies Din won the race last year in 1:48 2-5, and Anet won the  
year before in the same time. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier in the day, 4-5 favorite Stormy Jack, who is trained by  
Bob Baffert, won the $106,000 I'm Smokin Stakes for 2-year-olds 
bred in California for his second victory in as many starts. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Antley and carrying 117 pounds, Stormy Jack covered 5 1/2  
furlongs in 1:03 4-5 in beating Ditka by 3 1/2 lengths, and paid 
$3.60, $2.60 and $2.10. The win was worth $63,600, raising Stormy 
Jack's career earnings to $92,400. 
</P>
<P>
	Ditka returned $3 and $2.10, while third-place finisher  
Suspicious Minds paid $2.10 to show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
